    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-07-22T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-07-22T16:00:00-05:00" n="1284"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1284">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 138/142</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The</hi>
                    <gloss type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State</hi>
                    </gloss>
                    <hi rend="italic">to the Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_SPA1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stovall</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-07-22T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 22, 1915, 4 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>138. Ambassador London telegraphs 17th <persName>James Cook</persName> Trumbull
                    of Rockefeller Foundation experienced trouble in England because he carried
                    emergency passport issued by yourself on form printed in Switzerland instead of
                    regular form to take the place of regular passport issued by Department March
                    16. Apparently you took up Department passport because French consuls are
                    unwilling to visa passports of persons who have been in Germany, Austria or
                    Turkey. Department does not consider action taken in Trumbull case advisable. It
                    is believed that if this case had been fully explained to French Consulate or
                    Legation visa of Department passport might have been obtained.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
